that can see the stars this year right away.

46
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:54,800
But a few years from now, if we try for it...

47
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:57,050
We should go, shouldn't we?

48
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:00,470
I think that's what everyone wants, at least.

49
00:04:01,210 --> 00:04:04,890
Still... that's the place where Takako died.

50
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,320
It's not safe at all.

51
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:09,830
What should we do?

52
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:14,820
New Year's

53
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:14,820
From Syowa Station

54
00:04:13,390 --> 00:04:14,820
This is awful!

55
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:18,680
I bet Mom's spreading it all
over social media right now!

56
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:22,570
What's the big deal? It makes better 
advertising for the broadcast.

57
00:04:23,860 --> 00:04:24,760
Hinata?

58
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:27,200
Oh... do mine, too!

59
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,650
Oh? Your only New Year's 
card is to your manager?

60
00:04:30,650 --> 00:04:32,710
None for your friends from earlier?

61
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:35,510
Well... they're New Year's cards,

62
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:38,310
but they won't reach anyone until 
the boat gets back to Japan anyway.

63
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:39,380
I'm gonna hit the can!

64
00:04:41,370 --> 00:04:42,120
Ouch!

65
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,300
Stupid thing...

66
00:04:44,790 --> 00:04:46,390
Is she annoyed?

67
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:48,040
Did it hurt that much?

68
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,330
She seems a bit stressed out.

69
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:52,680
Shirase-chan, you're going, too?

70
00:05:02,990 --> 00:05:04,010
Piss off!

71
00:05:04,130 --> 00:05:05,370
Piss off!

72
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:07,420
Piss off, damn it!

73
00:05:09,770 --> 00:05:11,160
Stupid thing!

74
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:12,910
Piss off!

75
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,150
There you are!

76
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:45,610
The weather's cleared up,

77
00:05:45,610 --> 00:05:48,200
so they said they'd bring us along for 
the sea ice and geological testing!

78
00:05:48,770 --> 00:05:51,720
I'll prepare the camera, 
so think about your report!

79
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,310
Huh? Oh. Right.

80
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:54,660
Expedition! Expedition!

81
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:56,320
Don't forget, you said you'd do the report!

82
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,660
Don't claim later that 
you don't want to do it!

83
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,090
Um... Hinata...

84
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,610
About before...

85
00:06:01,610 --> 00:06:04,090
That was a test, so it won't cut the mustard.

86
00:06:04,090 --> 00:06:05,020
No—

87
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:07,160
Hurry up! They're heading out soon!

88
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,840
Coming!

89
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:14,350
We did this together three years ago.

90
00:06:14,630 --> 00:06:18,310
Takako-senpai just wanted to do everything.

91
00:06:18,650 --> 00:06:19,760
She did?

92
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:22,010
Yeah, she went all over.

93
00:06:22,010 --> 00:06:24,250
She was here, too, Shirase-chan!

94
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,610
Isn't that nice?

95
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:28,470
Yeah...

96
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,620
Take that!

97
00:06:34,810 --> 00:06:35,960
What's that?

98
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:39,380
It's all ice up ahead, so we're 
digging a hole with steam.

99
00:06:39,980 --> 00:06:43,390
After that, I think we went to Rundvågshetta.

100
00:06:43,390 --> 00:06:45,550
Sounds like a powerful name!

101
00:06:45,820 --> 00:06:49,140
It's a place with exposed rock.

102
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:53,070
If you ask Nobue-san, 
she might take you there.

103
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:53,680
Let's go!

104
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:58,190
<i>Sea Ice here! Nobue-san at geology? 
Do you read? Over!</i>

105
00:06:58,970 --> 00:07:02,460
<i>Haven't heard from him since Christmas.</i>

106
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:05,470
<i>The garnet he gave me two years ago...</i>

107
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:08,990
Dry rocks and dry love...

108
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:12,470
No email. No nothing from Yu-kun.

109
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:16,620
<i>She's currently unable to talk. Over.</i>

110
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:24,600
It's cold!

111
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:27,380
Seriously. The difference in 
air temperature is extreme...

112
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:31,060
Please, stop it!

113
00:07:31,450 --> 00:07:32,840
Look! It's amazing!

114
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:33,950
So cold!

115
00:07:35,020 --> 00:07:36,480
Watch for animals

116
00:07:44,890 --> 00:07:47,680
Antarctica really is amazing, huh?

117
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,440
It's neat to see it from this angle...

118
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,120
The sky is flowing by!

119
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:59,900
I wonder if we'll see an aurora?

120
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:01,300
At night, maybe.

121
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,630
But it won't become night

122
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,870
during the time we're here.

123
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:08,580
Hinata.

124
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:13,860
Is something bothering you?

125
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:15,390
Bothering me?

126
00:08:15,580 --> 00:08:19,150
Well, my lips get so 
chapped with the dry air,

127
00:08:19,150 --> 00:08:21,140
but my lip balm is frozen,
so it's hard to put on.

128
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:22,660
I know how you feel!

129
00:08:22,660 --> 00:08:25,250
It really is hard! 
It's like your skin is peeling off.

130
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,510
Right?

131
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:27,650
So dry!

132
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:30,150
Be Careful Going Outside

133
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:30,440
<i>All crew outdoors, please seek
shelter in the main building</i>

134
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:33,160
<i>or a building with emergency rations.</i>

135
00:08:36,010 --> 00:08:37,370
It's not getting better at all.

136
00:08:38,010 --> 00:08:40,040
You should probably give up on it.

137
00:08:40,290 --> 00:08:41,870
Where'd Shirase go, anyway?

138
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:44,550
Someone asked her earlier if 
she knew how to play Mahjong...

139
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:46,450
For real? Can she?

140
00:08:46,450 --> 00:08:49,550
It sounded fun, so I looked 
over her shoulder, but...

141
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:54,530
Hey, how do you read the one that 
looks like a person next to a five?

142
00:08:54,530 --> 00:08:55,350
"Go."

143
00:08:55,350 --> 00:08:57,870
Hey, you've got some white ones 
mixed up in your reserves.

144
00:08:58,190 --> 00:08:59,640
They're not reserves.

145
00:09:00,460 --> 00:09:02,390
That bird is so cute!

146
00:09:02,390 --> 00:09:04,140
"Get out!"

147
00:09:04,490 --> 00:09:05,320
...she said.

148
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,620
That's rather cruel.

149
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:09,460
Right? I was only asking questions!

150
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:12,460
Shirase's always been testy!

