00:10:13,090 --> 00:10:15,340
National Antarctic Research Center
(To Miyake Hinata) Hanyu Daisan High School Track Team

179
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,820
you quit the track team and
quit school so suddenly

180
00:10:30,820 --> 00:10:32,150
We wish we'd said something to the older girls. 
We're sorry for leaving you all alone.

181
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,020
Shirase?

182
00:10:34,450 --> 00:10:35,430
Are you...

183
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,070
Hinata-chan?

184
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:39,280
National Antarctic Research Center
(To Miyake Hinata)

185
00:10:40,490 --> 00:10:41,750
You saw it?

186
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:43,500
Just a little.

187
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:46,540
But that was addressed to Hinata-san...

188
00:10:46,540 --> 00:10:48,500
How could you do something like that?

189
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:52,500
But... but I was worried, so...

190
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:55,510
You seemed so mad about something, and...

191
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:58,260
you wouldn't say anything...

192
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,610
You were mad?

193
00:10:59,610 --> 00:11:01,010
What, you saw it?

194
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:02,530
You should have said something!

195
00:11:02,530 --> 00:11:03,980
I was worried.

196
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:06,270
I thought you were hiding something!

197
00:11:06,530 --> 00:11:09,270
Something you weren't telling us!

198
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:14,030
We're sorry for leaving you all alone.

199
00:11:25,510 --> 00:11:28,950
Let me tell you in advance, 
it's a totally gross story.

200
00:11:29,350 --> 00:11:32,550
I don't want to talk about it, 
and I hate that you asked me.

201
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:33,710
Just tell us.

202
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:41,180
In short, it's about why 
I stopped going to club.

203
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:46,640
It's the competition, 
so the fastest people should go.

204
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,970
Your year and stuff doesn't matter!

205
00:11:48,970 --> 00:11:52,040
But for the third-years, 
this will be their last competition...

206
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:54,790
Exactly! It would be more 
rude to go easy on them!

207
00:11:56,950 --> 00:11:59,320
Two hundred meter, Miyake Hinata.

208
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:01,170
Yes!

209
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:08,880
Didn't you say something to that idiot?

210
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:12,070
O-Of course... we told
her to be more sensitive...

211
00:12:13,170 --> 00:12:17,330
In that instant, nothing mattered to me.

212
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:24,250
But it does matter! 
They're the ones to blame.

213
00:12:25,420 --> 00:12:27,620
Humans can be scary, huh?

214
00:12:27,620 --> 00:12:35,020
After I quit, they kept spreading all 
kinds of rumors to lay the blame on me.

215
00:12:35,330 --> 00:12:39,070
Is that why you quit school?

216
00:12:40,410 --> 00:12:41,480
Hinata.

217
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:45,740
Sorry I'm a loser!

218
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:49,110
Then the ones who sent the email are...

219
00:12:49,110 --> 00:12:51,610
Yeah. My old teammates.

220
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:54,200
They want to talk during the broadcast.

221
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:58,000
They said they were proud their 
friend went to Antarctica.

222
00:12:59,110 --> 00:13:01,880
Though mainly, I was thinking 
"Oh, were we friends?"

223
00:13:09,610 --> 00:13:10,570
Well?

224
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,960
What? Different from what you imagined?

225
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:19,010
It's almost otherworldly, huh?

226
00:13:19,010 --> 00:13:20,680
Oh, uh, yeah!

227
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:22,440
What an unusual color!

228
00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:25,050
We'll set up a tent and 
antenna down that way.

229
00:13:25,050 --> 00:13:26,270
Okay!

230
00:13:27,950 --> 00:13:28,750
Hey!

231
00:13:29,420 --> 00:13:32,700
How long are you gonna 
drag this out? Forget it.

232
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:35,020
I don't like being treated this way.

233
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:35,930
But...

234
00:13:35,930 --> 00:13:38,710
Look, why do you think I came to Antarctica?

235
00:13:39,650 --> 00:13:41,210
Because there's nothing here!

236
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:46,210
I wanted to go to an empty place 
with no one to tie me down!

237
00:13:46,530 --> 00:13:48,220
Look, isn't it amazing?

238
00:13:48,570 --> 00:13:52,470
Glaciers! Strata! Water from melted snow!

239
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:56,360
Colors and shapes I've never seen before!

240
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:59,100
We're in a place isolated 
from everything we know,

241
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:02,980
a completely different world 
from where we've been before.

242
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:05,230
That's what I came here to enjoy!

243
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:07,830
But it doesn't mean anything
if you're all sad, right?

244
00:14:10,170 --> 00:14:12,610
Got it. Then we'll forget it!

245
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:14,380
First, we've got camping to do!

246
00:14:14,380 --> 00:14:16,240
It's not a game!

247
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:17,670
Shirase?

248
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,370
It does mean something.

249
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,040
It absolutely does mean something!

250
00:14:32,170 --> 00:14:34,440
It's like a sci-fi movie, isn't it?

251
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:37,030
Want to drink the water? It's delicious.

252
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:38,180
We can drink it?

253
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:41,770
In a way, it's the cleanest 
water on the planet.

254
00:14:41,770 --> 00:14:44,040
Hardly anyone's ever touched it,

255
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:46,940
and it doesn't get warm 
enough to breed bacteria.

256
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:48,580
I'm first!

257
00:14:48,580 --> 00:14:49,190
No fair!

258
00:14:54,260 --> 00:14:55,080
How is it?

259
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:56,490
Delicious!

260
00:14:57,460 --> 00:14:59,000
I want to try, too!

261
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:03,950
You're right! It's delicious and cold!

262
00:15:03,950 --> 00:15:05,500
It really hits the spot!

263
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,050
Want some, Shirase-chan?

264
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:09,330
Later.

265
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:11,840
We got through.

266
00:15:12,970 --> 00:15:13,980
Talk.

267
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,720
Me?

268
00:15:16,810 --> 00:15:22,180
U-Um... this is Kobuchizawa at Rundvågshetta.

269
00:15:22,180 --> 00:15:23,130
Over.

270
00:15:23,770 --> 00:15:26,350
<i>This is Syowa. We read you loud and clear.</i>

271
00:15:26,830 --> 00:15:28,890
How is the scenery? Over.

272
00:15:28,890 --> 00:15:33,130
<i>Um... It's like we're surrounded by cake.</i>

273
00:15:33,130 --> 00:15:34,050
Cake?

274
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:36,360
Takako said the same thing.

275
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:39,300
The minute we got there,
"I want to eat chocolate cake!"

276
00:15:40,290 --> 00:15:41,280
My mother said that?

277
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:44,400
It's the best natural water I've ever had!

278
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:54,390
Like this?

279
00:15:54,390 --> 00:15:55,000
Perfect.

280
00:15:55,350 --> 00:15:57,980
Kimari-san, you're good 
at the strangest things.

281
00:15:57,980 --> 00:15:59,260
That's not strange, is it?

282
00:16:00,210 --> 00:16:02,260
Can they see this on the satellites?

283
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:06,810
Yes. We use these so they can check 
our location on the satellites.

284
00:16:06,810 --> 00:16:09,140
It will definitely show up.

285
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:11,030
It's not taking it now.

286
00:16:12,310 --> 00:16:13,150
Yu-kun...

287
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:17,240
Yu-kun!

288
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:17,240
Um...

289
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:19,900
Don't let it bother you. 
She does this constantly.

290
00:16:22,550 --> 00:16:26,610
We even put a plate here. 
Someone's watching, huh?

291
00:16:28,090 --> 00:16:29,040
It's nothing personal, okay?

292
00:16:43,350 --> 00:16:44,550
What bliss!

293
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:47,000
Especially since it's getting colder.

294
00:16:47,850 --> 00:16:49,060
And now it's time for...

295
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:50,440
Ta-da!

296
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,320
Next time we get hot water 
going, let's make tamagoyaki!

297
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,440
You really like tamagoyaki, huh?

298
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:59,060
She did eat a lot of it for 
breakfast in Singapore!

299
00:16:59,410 --> 00:17:00,300
Hinata.

300
00:17:01,540 --> 00:17:03,710
I'm going to collect water. Come with me.

301
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:07,130
We don't have enough? 
Sorry I used it all earlier...

302
00:17:07,130 --> 00:17:08,010
Kimari-san.

303
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,170
Wow, it's freezing when the wind blows.

304
00:17:17,420 --> 00:17:19,270
I could just die right now!

305
00:17:19,270 --> 00:17:25,360
I've been thinking about what 
I'd do in your position.

306
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:31,440
We're sorry for leaving you all alone.

307
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:28,590
If someone had treated me so awfully,

308
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:31,440
then called me up out of the blue, 
as though nothing happened,

309
00:17:32,230 --> 00:17:35,250
wanting to apologize for the 
permanent damage they'd done...

310
00:17:35,690 --> 00:17:36,880
Hey, look...

311
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:38,820
I couldn't be okay with it.

312
00:17:38,820 --> 00:17:40,330
I couldn't smile.

313
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:44,070
You're not me, though.

314
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,550
I know, but...

315
00:17:47,390 --> 00:17:48,580
I know, but...

316
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,340
Shirase.

317
00:17:52,450 --> 00:17:53,330
Take off your gloves.

318
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,090
Hand them over.

319
00:18:01,610 --> 00:18:02,590
Your hands are enough.

320
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:06,150
Shirase, you're so annoying, 
the way you keep talking and talking.

321
00:18:08,150 --> 00:18:09,370
Thanks.

322
00:18:10,060 --> 00:18:14,450
I'm sorry. I guess I'm still scared.

323
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:16,290
Hinata...

324
00:18:16,290 --> 00:18:17,680
I'm scared.

325
00:18:19,150 --> 00:18:20,860
But we...

326
00:18:22,690 --> 00:18:24,990
I said your hands were enough, remember?

327
00:18:32,470 --> 00:18:34,680
Thanks for bringing me along.

328
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,880
Tamagoyaki's ready!

329
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:41,540
Okay! We're on our way!

330
00:18:43,740 --> 00:18:44,790
C'mon!

331
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:52,020
12/31
Choose Your Own New Year's Soba
Tempura
Mochi
Plain

332
00:18:52,270 --> 00:18:53,780
You suck! They're not supposed
to be flat noodles!

333
00:18:53,780 --> 00:18:55,030
They're thin enough!

334
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:55,920
Start from scratch.

335
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,030
Really?!

336
00:18:57,630 --> 00:18:59,830
<i>Ready to roll in ten minutes.</i>

337
00:18:59,830 --> 00:19:00,910
Understood!

338
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:03,240
My sun tan never recovered...

339
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,280
It's proof that you're 
enjoying Antarctica.

340
00:19:06,090 --> 00:19:06,970
Hey.

341
00:19:08,740 --> 00:19:11,780
Do you think I'll feel 
better if I forgive them?

342
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:13,820
You want to forgive them?

343
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:16,740
If it would make me feel better, I might.

344
00:19:16,740 --> 00:19:22,120
But when I imagine them looking all relieved 
afterwords, it gets under my skin.

345
00:19:23,590 --> 00:19:24,760
"Piss off"?

346
00:19:26,460 --> 00:19:27,380
Yeah.

347
00:19:28,490 --> 00:19:30,300
I'm a pretty petty person, aren't I?

348
00:19:34,910 --> 00:19:36,620
It's 9:00 AM here.

349
00:19:36,620 --> 00:19:38,740
A six-hour difference from Japan...

350
00:19:38,740 --> 00:19:41,030
Before we start, may I say one thing?

351
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:45,720
Shirase-chan?

352
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:49,800
I beg your pardon, but could 
you leave Miyake Hinata alone?

353
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:50,950
Shirase...

354
00:19:51,330 --> 00:19:56,230
You might think Hinata has been holding a 
grudge against you since she quit school,

355
00:19:56,880 --> 00:19:59,830
that she's been suffering badly.

356
00:20:00,540 --> 00:20:02,880
Maybe you think she spends every day crying,

357
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:05,030
thinking about what happened to her.

358
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,850
But...

359
00:20:07,650 --> 00:20:08,490
But...

360
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:14,090
But that's not true!

361
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:19,170
Hinata-chan is having a super, 
amazing fun time with us!

362
00:20:19,170 --> 00:20:23,190
She's having a really fulfilling trip 
of the sort you can't get where you are!

363
00:20:23,190 --> 00:20:23,860
Hey!

364
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:27,020
Hinata is already looking forward!

365
00:20:27,020 --> 00:20:29,270
She's already walking!

366
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:31,510
She's taking her steps with us!

367
00:20:31,510 --> 00:20:32,020
Shirase!

368
00:20:32,020 --> 00:20:35,130
It's fine! It's friendship!

369
00:20:35,460 --> 00:20:39,040
Unlike Hinata, I'm a real jerk, 
so I'll say it outright.

370
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:42,500
You can't live your lives in 
this halfway state forever!

371
00:20:43,220 --> 00:20:45,370
You hurt someone and made them suffer!

372
00:20:45,370 --> 00:20:47,260
Now you get to live with that!

373
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:50,140
That's what you get for hurting someone!

374
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:53,100
That's what you get for hurting my friend!

375
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:58,530
Shirase!

376
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,550
You think you can come crawling back now?

377
00:21:07,820 --> 00:21:09,000
Piss off!

378
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:16,410
Let's get things ready.

379
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:20,220
Okay.

380
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:28,960
<i>The year is nearing its end.</i>

381
00:21:29,840 --> 00:21:31,530
Will it be on TV?

382
00:21:31,530 --> 00:21:33,640
Last year's video, yeah.

383
00:21:34,590 --> 00:21:35,710
It's here!

384
00:21:35,710 --> 00:21:40,730
Yu-kun! Yu-kun! Yu-kun!

385
00:21:41,090 --> 00:21:42,290
Let's do it, too!

386
00:21:42,290 --> 00:21:43,450
Casting away our worldly desires!

387
00:21:43,450 --> 00:21:44,480
You mean...

388
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:46,600
...like this?

389
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,730
Let's bash the bad thoughts 
away, Hinata-chan!

390
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:50,980
What if we break it?

391
00:21:51,650 --> 00:21:53,490
So what if you do? It's just a drum can.

392
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:56,370
Good point!

393
00:21:56,810 --> 00:21:58,850
Okay, let's do the first one together!

394
00:22:00,550 --> 00:22:02,500
One, two...

395
00:23:33,010 --> 00:23:36,520
A Place Further
Than the Universe

